I do agree that some of us &quot;whine&quot; too much, but to be fair, I think we're only &quot;whining&quot; since Enchanter charm does indirectly have an effect on us (as I mentioned in my previous thread)...<br>
<br>
For the first time EVER, I agree with Noonie about the Pre-60 Charms... Pre-PoP, Enchanters could charm-kill the entire front section of the Chardok zone before repops while a similarly equipped 6 man group could not. Differences in power as outrageous as this just hurts the game in the long run... I have always believed that the original reason for Charm was for crowd-control in group situations. Charm should never be a long term replacement for the need to have other players. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=60465">Xerphanis</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Arch Convoker</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=warblekthedamned>WarblekTheDamned</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(1/14/03 4:48:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=408.topic&index=55>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   .</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
