Hehe, don't play a bard do ya, at 45 my bard can swarm kite infinite (as many as I can find), non casting even cons.<br>
<br>
I agree with you though, which is why I won't complain with this &quot;type&quot; of change, even if it only reduces the chanters charmed DPS a little bit (still outdamaging 3-4 other classes), I agree that they should be able to pit 1 on 1 and get 2 rather easy kills with some risk (less risk than we would have with charming obviously), even cutting their ability to Mass AA by 40-50% (which is what this would do if it went live) is enough to satisfy me.  I LOVE grouping with enchanters, and I love it when they charm kill in a group (even though my pet will die before theirs gets hit, which there is a solution for that makes it safer for the enchanter/group).<br>
<br>
This change, while it is visually insignificant, would bring the enchanters back down into line with other classes, and still give them a great solo'ing ability (which they should have, they have always had).  Plus it would add a little more risk to their solo'ing as they should have, they are CC, they know how to handle risk, they have the tools to do so.<br>
<br>
I am behind this change if it goes live, if it doesn't I am behind a similar change of sorts.  Mainly anything that brings their potential DPS down a couple notches inline with other classes. <br>
<br>
Yeah, we take a hit too, acceptable losses to bring us closer to balance, JT aa while you can, enchanters pound those aa's out before the change (in case it would go live), at least you guys have been able to experience insane aa pharming, the likes of which melee's and healers will never see.  Then you can sit back and come back to the same rates as the rest of us.  <br>
<br>
